// Smoke-test deferred lighting BXDF: the engine's built-in whole-surface model, used by the smoke materials so
// their cooks satisfy the per-material BXDF requirement. Pulled into the cook-generated deferred lighting
// dispatch module (which #defines NWB_DEFERRED_BXDF_FUNCTION to this model's entry name). The deferred lighting
// framework (NwbBxdfSurface, the scene light list, the shadow accessor, the engine BRDF helpers) is in scope.
float3 NWB_DEFERRED_BXDF_FUNCTION(NwbBxdfSurface surface, uint shadowMask){
    return nwbSceneApplyLighting(
        surface.baseColor,
        surface.normal,
        float4(0.0, 0.0, 0.0, 1.0),
        surface.worldPosition,
        shadowMask
    );
}


